{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a12db5ed54240f2d0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a research sub-agent. You have WebSearch and WebFetch tools (load them first via ToolSearch with query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\" if needed).\n\nRESEARCH ANGLE: The \"generation-verification gap\" / \"verification is easier than generation\" idea, and the ceiling claim that a self-improving system cannot reliably produce solutions BETTER than its verifier can validate.\n\nFind specific, quotable sources on:\n- Leopold Aschenbrenner \"Situational Awareness\" — discussion of recursive self-improvement and that verification/evaluation feasibility gates the loop. (situational-awareness.ai)\n- The general \"verification is easier than generation\" principle (P vs NP intuition, Andrej Karpathy on verification, RL works where verification is cheap).\n- The \"verifier's law\" / Jason Wei \"Asymmetry of verification and verifier's law\" (2025).\n- The claim that an evolutionary/RSI loop only SEARCHES within / amplifies what the verifier can discriminate and what the base model latently can do — it does not exceed verifier discriminative power. Goodhart-adjacent ceiling.\n\nRun 4-6 WebSearch queries. Then WebFetch the 4-6 best primary sources. Extract exact wording.\n\nSearch terms: \"generation verification gap LLM\", \"verification easier than generation\", \"verifier's law Jason Wei asymmetry of verification\", \"Karpathy verification reinforcement learning\", \"Aschenbrenner recursive self-improvement situational awareness\", \"can't bootstrap above verifier\", \"verifier ceiling RSI\".\n\nOUTPUT: Return a list of 5-10 FALSIFIABLE CLAIMS. Each claim must be:\n- A single concrete factual sentence\n- Followed by the EXACT source URL\n- Followed by a short verbatim quote or close paraphrase supporting it\nDo not pad. Only return claims you actually found support for in fetched pages."},"uuid":"2944a22a-c4b5-4163-a991-1df9159b91ce","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:21.243Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
