{"parentUuid":"65a43624-6dec-4a4e-8392-aee8aced3b5e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a12db5ed54240f2d0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1E8py3duktdwD25hWVBzj","type":"tool_result","content":"# Key Quotes from \"Asymmetry of Verification and Verifier's Rule\"\n\n**On Asymmetry of Verification:**\n\"Asymmetry of verification is the idea that some tasks are much easier to verify than to solve.\"\n\n**On Verifier's Rule Definition:**\n\"The ease of training AI to solve a task is proportional to how verifiable the task is.\"\n\n**On AI Solving Verifiable Tasks:**\n\"All tasks that are possible to solve and easy to verify will be solved by AI.\"\n\n**On Why RL Works with Cheap Verification:**\n\"In RL terms, ability to verify solutions is equivalent to ability to create an RL environment.\"\n\n**On the Importance of Verifiability:**\n\"The amount of learning that occurs in neural networks is maximized when the above criteria are satisfied; you can take a lot of gradient steps where each step has a lot of signal.\"\n\n**On Limits/Ceilings Related to Verifiability:**\n\"We will likely have a jagged edge of intelligence, where AI is much smarter at verifiable tasks because it's so much easier to solve verifiable tasks.\""}]},"uuid":"c102281b-09dc-4200-9cdc-beb533a47796","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:47.445Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":199760,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Key Quotes from \"Asymmetry of Verification and Verifier's Rule\"\n\n**On Asymmetry of Verification:**\n\"Asymmetry of verification is the idea that some tasks are much easier to verify than to solve.\"\n\n**On Verifier's Rule Definition:**\n\"The ease of training AI to solve a task is proportional to how verifiable the task is.\"\n\n**On AI Solving Verifiable Tasks:**\n\"All tasks that are possible to solve and easy to verify will be solved by AI.\"\n\n**On Why RL Works with Cheap Verification:**\n\"In RL terms, ability to verify solutions is equivalent to ability to create an RL environment.\"\n\n**On the Importance of Verifiability:**\n\"The amount of learning that occurs in neural networks is maximized when the above criteria are satisfied; you can take a lot of gradient steps where each step has a lot of signal.\"\n\n**On Limits/Ceilings Related to Verifiability:**\n\"We will likely have a jagged edge of intelligence, where AI is much smarter at verifiable tasks because it's so much easier to solve verifiable tasks.\"","durationMs":3438,"url":"https://www.jasonwei.net/blog/asymmetry-of-verification-and-verifiers-law"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"65a43624-6dec-4a4e-8392-aee8aced3b5e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
