 he corrected the model\" regarding agentic coding.\n\n**On outsourcing thinking:**\n\"You can outsource your thinking but you can't outsource your understanding.\" (Karpathy citing a tweet he \"thinks about every other day\")\n\n## Paraphrased Karpathy Claims (Not Direct Quotes)\n\n- He described models as \"jagged entities\" that spike in verifiable domains (code, math) while stagnating in unverifiable ones\n- He explained the car wash failure as evidence of undertraining in domains lacking clean verifiers\n- He advised founders that labs will eventually own clearly verifiable domains; opportunities exist in verifiable-but-unverified areas\n- He referenced the \"bitter lesson\" regarding neural networks outperforming human heuristics\n- He noted that code output can be \"bloaty\" with \"copy-paste and awkward abstractions\" despite passing verification","durationMs":5969,"url":"https://www.mindstudio.ai/blog/andrej-karpathy-verifiability-thesis-ai-superhuman-code-fails-car-wash"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e3fbd5bb-3831-4e1b-bd7d-840dbc5df455","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
