{"parentUuid":"2eff5235-40bf-4eca-a4c2-c48aa818e0a5","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"b83cd85c-215e-4dfb-b12b-82fa27341e0f","agentId":"a12db5ed54240f2d0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HdgZWzuMEkasLgM34yy21B","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"\"Mind the Gap\" self-improvement LLMs generation-verification gap arxiv\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"[2412.02674] Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.02674\"},{\"title\":\"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mtJSMcF3ek\"},{\"title\":\"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=Hgv0tqgaiA\"},{\"title\":\"MIND THE GAP: EXAMINING THE SELF-IMPROVEMENT ...\",\"url\":\"https://proceedings.iclr.cc/paper_files/paper/2025/file/63943ee9fe347f3d95892cf87d9a42e6-Paper-Conference.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2412.02674\"},{\"title\":\"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/386419076_Mind_the_Gap_Examining_the_Self-Improvement_Capabilities_of_Large_Language_Models\"},{\"title\":\"When Does Verification Pay Off? A Closer Look at LLMs as Solution Verifiers\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.02304\"},{\"title\":\"A Training-Free Regeneration Paradigm: Contrastive Reflection Memory Guided Self-Verification and Self-Improvement\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.20441\"}]\n\nI found the paper you're looking for! Here are the key findings:\n\n**Paper Details:**\n\"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models\" explores self-improvement as a mechanism in Large Language Model pre-training, post-training and test-time inference.\n\n**Main Framework:**\nThe study explores a framework where the model verifies its own outputs, filters or reweights data based on this verification, and distills the filtered data.\n\n**Key Contribution - Generation-Verification Gap:**\nThe paper provides a mathematical formulation for self-improvement, which is largely governed by a quantity formalized as the generation-verification gap.\n\n**Major Finding:**\nThrough experiments with various model families and tasks, the researchers discover a scaling phenomenon of self-improvement -- a variant of the generation-verification gap scales monotonically with the model pre-training flops.\n\n**Additional Insights:**\nThe work also examines when self-improvement is possible, an iterative self-improvement procedure, and ways to improve its performance.\n\nThe paper was published on arXiv as preprint 2412.02674 and appears to have been accepted to ICLR 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"5d589f82-4679-494f-879b-123d8ac47439","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:36:08.533Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"\"Mind the Gap\" self-improvement LLMs generation-verification gap arxiv","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_011GVbAuLrHacynw3vPMXZaJ","content":[{"title":"[2412.02674] Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2412.02674"},{"title":"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=mtJSMcF3ek"},{"title":"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement","url":"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=Hgv0tqgaiA"},{"title":"MIND THE GAP: EXAMINING THE SELF-IMPROVEMENT ...","url":"https://proceedings.iclr.cc/paper_files/paper/2025/file/63943ee9fe347f3d95892cf87d9a42e6-Paper-Conference.pdf"},{"title":"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2412.02674"},{"title":"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models","url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/386419076_Mind_the_Gap_Examining_the_Self-Improvement_Capabilities_of_Large_Language_Models"},{"title":"When Does Verification Pay Off? A Closer Look at LLMs as Solution Verifiers","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.02304"},{"title":"A Training-Free Regeneration Paradigm: Contrastive Reflection Memory Guided Self-Verification and Self-Improvement","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2603.20441"}]},"I found the paper you're looking for! Here are the key findings:\n\n**Paper Details:**\n\"Mind the Gap: Examining the Self-Improvement Capabilities of Large Language Models\" explores self-improvement as a mechanism in Large Language Model pre-training, post-training and test-time inference.\n\n**Main Framework:**\nThe study explores a framework where the model verifies its own outputs, filters or reweights data based on this verification, and distills the filtered data.\n\n**Key Contribution - Generation-Verification Gap:**\nThe paper provides a mathematical formulation for self-improvement, which is largely governed by a quantity formalized as the generation-verification gap.\n\n**Major Finding:**\nThrough experiments with various model families and tasks, the researchers discover a scaling phenomenon of self-improvement -- a variant of the generation-verification gap scales monotonically with the model pre-training flops.\n\n**Additional Insights:**\nThe work also examines when self-improvement is possible, an iterative self-improvement procedure, and ways to improve its performance.\n\nThe paper was published on arXiv as preprint 2412.02674 and appears to have been accepted to ICLR 2025."],"durationSeconds":6.943847374999896,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2eff5235-40bf-4eca-a4c2-c48aa818e0a5","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183"